[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:QJ8763.AK8.8.K75 K95.T97542.A3.Q2 A4.QJ6.7642.A963 T2.3.KQJT95.JT84"]
[BoardVersionToken "d1290c72303a75a315ce08ec467569feefbdf61634cdbd7d2f1e118a7ce428c2"]
[Student "S"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/two_over_one"]
[Auction "E"]
1S Pass 1NT Pass 2S Pass 3S Pass 4S Pass Pass Pass
{East opens 1\S.  
With 11 points you cannot respond 2\C. So you bid 1NT, which is forcing for 1 round. 
East rebids 2\s, promising at least 6 \ss and denying a 4-card side suit.

You are strong enough to invite to game, and with the known 8-card fit you say 3\S.
East has a little extra so he bids 4\S, which is a pretty good contract.}

